feat(docs): tabbed trailer documents with versioning + soft-delete

Refactor the per-trailer Documents tab from a flat list into a 4-tab
checklist UI (Vehicle / Insurance / Contracts / Tracking) with required
vs optional types per tab, automatic version chains, manager-only
approve/reject flow, and soft-delete that preserves audit history.

## Backend
- Extended trailer_documents: category, document_type, status, version,
  parent_document_id (self-FK), is_current, rejection_reason, reviewed_by,
  reviewed_at, file_size, mime_type, deleted_at. Old document_category
  column kept nullable for the backfill window.
- Indexes: tenant, trailer, (trailer, type), (trailer, type, current),
  plus a unique partial index on (trailer_id, document_type) WHERE
  is_current AND deleted_at IS NULL — DB-level guarantee of one active
  current per type per trailer.
- Shared catalog (shared/document-types.ts) drives both server validation
  and UI checklist; adding a doc type is a single edit.
- storage.createTrailerDocument auto-versions inside a transaction.
- New storage.setTrailerDocumentStatus + PATCH /:docId/status
  (manager-only). Rejects soft-deleted rows (404).
- DELETE is soft: sets deleted_at, leaves the object intact, idempotent
  on re-call, and promotes the next non-deleted version to current.
- Listings + chain lookups filter deleted_at IS NULL.
- Audit log entries for uploaded / version_added / status_changed /
  deleted (with softDelete=true).
- Backfill (server/migrations/backfill-trailer-docs.ts) is truly
  idempotent: groups legacy rows by (tenant, trailer, mapped_type), and
  for any group containing at least one un-migrated row, reloads ALL
  siblings (including already-migrated) and rebuilds the entire chain
  inside a transaction, so partial reruns cannot create duplicate v1
  roots or break parent_document_id lineage.

## Frontend (client/src/pages/assets.tsx)
- New TrailerDocumentsTab with shadcn Tabs + per-category panel rendering
  every catalog type (current file, status badge, version, uploader/
  reviewer info, history popover, upload/replace/view/delete buttons,
  approve/reject for managers).
- Removed the old DnD reorder UI and SortableDocumentRow.

## i18n
- Added assets.docs.* keys (categories, types, statuses, actions, reject
  dialog) in en-US and pt-BR.

## Drift
- Rejection reason is REQUIRED instead of optional (better
  accountability).
- API returns flat doc list; client groups using the shared catalog
  (avoids duplicating grouping logic).
